{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e3eb3289-6ea8-4917-a759-1bbcc355c9cd","content":"Here are the MSBuild evaluation performance issues in this project:\n\n---\n\n### 1. Expensive Property Function — File I/O during evaluation\n**File:** `EvalHeavy.csproj`, line 13\n```xml\n<BuildNotes>$([System.IO.File]::ReadAllText('build-notes.txt'))</BuildNotes>\n```\nReading file contents via `System.IO.File` during evaluation is costly. This runs on every evaluation pass (design-time builds, restores, IDE refreshes). Move file reading to a target that executes only at build time instead.\n\n---\n\n### 2. Overly broad glob pattern\n**File:** `EvalHeavy.csproj`, line 9\n```xml\n<AdditionalFiles Include=\"**\\*.*\" Exclude=\"**\\bin\\**;**\\obj\\**\" />\n```\nThe `**\\*.*` recursive wildcard forces MSBuild to enumerate the entire directory tree during evaluation. This scales poorly as the repo grows. Narrow the glob to specific extensions or directories.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Deep chained imports (3 levels)\n```\nEvalHeavy.csproj → level1.props → level2.props → level3.props\n```\nEach import adds an XML parse and evaluation pass. Here each file only sets a single property—these could be collapsed into one `.props` file to reduce import depth and evaluation overhead.\n\n---\n\n### Summary of recommendations\n\n| Issue | Fix |\n|-------|-----|\n| `File::ReadAllText` in property | Move to a build-time target or use a `ReadLinesFromFile` task |\n| `**\\*.*` glob | Restrict to needed file types (e.g., `**\\*.txt`) |\n| 3-level import chain | Flatten into a single props file |\n\nThe biggest offender is the file-read property function—it defeats MSBuild's evaluation caching and re-runs on every IDE evaluation cycle.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"7b579799-d8ff-49a6-af2b-6ebae32da19e","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Now I have a complete picture of the project. Let me analyze the MSBuild evaluation performance issues.","outputTokens":488,"requestId":"F019:149EED:2872EDB:2CB5179:69F94590"},"id":"dda7dec7-1580-4c53-b73d-28b09d55213a","timestamp":"2026-05-05T01:19:26.106Z","parentId":"520a8a75-1b89-4177-8ae5-a96c13db9707"}
